title Twilio Voice Session Setup

|Twilio Network|
start
:Incoming phone call arrives;
:HTTP POST /incoming-call\n(or GET for initial handshake);

|FastAPI / server.py|
:Return TwiML Response:\n<Connect><Stream url='wss://{host}/media-stream'/>\n</Connect>;

|Twilio Network|
:Dial /media-stream WebSocket endpoint;

|FastAPI / server.py|
:@app.websocket('/media-stream')\nmedia_stream_endpoint(websocket) fires;
:manager.new_session(websocket)\n[TwilioWebSocketManager];

|TwilioHandler|
:Instantiate TwilioHandler(websocket)\n- playback_tracker = RealtimePlaybackTracker()\n- audio_buffer = []\n- startup_buffer = []\n- _mark_data = {}\n- _mark_counter = 0\n- _stream_sid = None\n- _startup_warmed = False;
note right
  Env config:
  STARTUP_BUFFER_CHUNKS (default=3)
  STARTUP_DELAY_S (default=0.0)
  Audio: g711_ulaw at 8kHz
end note

:handler.start();
:Create RealtimeAgent\n(name='Twilio Assistant'\ntools=[get_weather, get_current_time]);
:Create RealtimeRunner(agent);

if (OPENAI_API_KEY present?) then (no)
  #FFD6D6:Raise ValueError\n"API key not configured";
  stop
else (yes)
endif

:runner.run(\n  api_key=OPENAI_API_KEY,\n  model='gpt-realtime-1.5',\n  input_audio_format='g711_ulaw',\n  output_audio_format='g711_ulaw',\n  turn_detection=semantic_vad\n) → returns RealtimeSession;

|OpenAI Realtime API|
:Accept Realtime WebSocket connection\nfrom RealtimeRunner;
:Activate session (session.id assigned);

|TwilioHandler|
:session.enter()\nActivate RealtimeSession\n(subscribe to events);
:twilio_websocket.accept()\nComplete WebSocket handshake\nwith Twilio;

if (STARTUP_DELAY_S > 0?) then (yes)
  :asyncio.sleep(STARTUP_DELAY_S)\n[optional warm-up delay];
else (no)
endif

note right
  Three concurrent async tasks
  are spawned simultaneously via
  asyncio.gather() / create_task()
end note

fork
  |#E8F5E9|TwilioHandler — Task A|
  :_realtime_session_loop\n[OpenAI → Twilio];
  repeat
    :async for event in self.session;
    if (event.type?) then (audio)
      :Base64-encode audio bytes;
      :Send 'media' JSON\nto Twilio WS (streamSid, payload);
      :Increment _mark_counter;
      :Send 'mark' JSON to Twilio WS\n(mark_id → item_id + byte_count);
    elseif (audio_interrupted) then
      :Send 'clear' JSON\nto Twilio WS (streamSid)\n[interrupt ongoing playback];
    elseif (audio_end) then
      :Log audio_end event;
    else (other)
      :No-op;
    endif
  repeat while (session active?)

fork again
  |#EAF2FF|TwilioHandler — Task B|
  :_twilio_message_loop\n[Twilio → OpenAI];
  repeat
    :receive_text from Twilio WS;
    :Parse JSON event;
    if (event type?) then (connected)
      :Log connected;
    elseif (start) then
      :Capture _stream_sid\nfrom start.streamSid;
    elseif (media) then
      :Decode base64 µ-law audio payload;
      :Extend _audio_buffer;
      if (len(_audio_buffer)\n>= BUFFER_SIZE_BYTES\n(~400 bytes / 50ms)?) then (yes)
        :_flush_audio_buffer();
      else (no)
      endif
    elseif (mark) then
      :Lookup mark_id in _mark_data;
      :playback_tracker.on_play_bytes(\n  item_id, content_index,\n  placeholder_bytes\n);
      :Delete entry from _mark_data;
    else (stop)
      :Log stop;
    endif
  repeat while (connection active?)

fork again
  |#FFF8E1|TwilioHandler — Task C|
  :_buffer_flush_loop\n[Periodic fallback, 50ms];
  repeat
    :asyncio.sleep(50ms);
    if (buffer has data AND\ntime since last send > 100ms?) then (yes)
      :_flush_audio_buffer();
    else (no)
    endif
  repeat while (session active?)

end fork

note right
  _flush_audio_buffer logic:
  • If NOT warmed up → accumulate into startup_buffer
    – If startup_buffer >= N_chunks × BUFFER_SIZE_BYTES
      → session.send_audio(startup_buffer)
        mark _startup_warmed = True
    – Else keep buffering
  • If already warmed up
    → session.send_audio(buffer_data) immediately
end note

|FastAPI / server.py|
:await handler.wait_until_done()\n(waits on _twilio_message_loop task);

if (WebSocketDisconnect\nor Exception?) then (yes)
  #FFD6D6:Log error / disconnection\nand exit gracefully;
  stop
else (no)
  :Session completed normally;
  stop
endif

@enduml
